<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS BUMMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I have always voted Democratic . . . sometimes with enthusiasm and sometimes 
not. Had I known that Vice President George Bush would choose his team on the 
strength of their tennis prowess ("Tennis, Everyone?" by Paul Dean, Dec. 19), I 
might have made an exception in this last election. Who can fault men who like 
a game that is played on a court where service is a vital part of the game? The 
only problem is, it is also a game where love means nothing. Maybe I voted the 
right way after all! Time will tell. 
</P>
<P>
MARJORIE L. SCHWARTZ 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
