<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Fox Network, which long has been talking about expanding its prime-time 
programming from two nights to three, has made it official and will add Monday 
to its lineup come fall. "Fox has come a long way in two years," Michael 
Fisher, chairman of the network's Board of Governors, told network affiliates 
here over the weekend. "We are undeniably a force to be reckoned with in the 
industry." The network now programs prime time on Saturday and Sunday nights. 
The new Monday lineup has a start date of Sept. 11 and will be chosen from 25 
pending projects. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
