<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After 26 years as a TV series star, actor-director-producer-writer Michael 
Landon says: "I don't think I want to be in a series again." Landon, 51, who 
starred as Little Joe Cartwright in "Bonanza" for 14 years (1959-73), as 
Charles Ingalls (Pa) in "Little House on the Prairie" for eight (1974-82) and 
as Earthbound angel Jonathan Smith for four years in NBC's recently-finished 
"Highway to Heaven," told The Times that he prefers to concentrate on producing 
TV projects rather than starring in them in the future. Meantime, he's enjoying 
"the first time off I've had in 30 years." ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
