<P>
SEX SHOW COSTS HOTEL'S KOSHER LICENSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JERUSALEM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The chief rabbi of Tiberias has revoked the kosher food license of a hotel for 
allowing a naked couple to have sex in a helicopter hovering above its pool 
during a New Year's party, the Jerusalem Post said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said the 20-minute live aerial sex act, the main attraction of 
the sold-out party at the Tiberias Club Hotel, was watched by guests from their 
bedrooms. 
</P>
<P>
Chief Rabbi David Peretz said the hotel had sinned and did not deserve a 
license to serve kosher food. 
</P>
<P>
"The directors of the hotel are completely nuts," Tiberias Mayor Yigal Bibi was 
quoted by the newspaper as saying. 
</P>
