<HEADLINE>
<P>
49ERS FAVORED BY 6 IN SUPER BOWL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAS VEGAS, Nev. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The San Francisco 49ers were made 6-point favorites over the Cincinnati Bengals 
in the Super Bowl following their championship game victories Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The 49ers beat Chicago, 28-3, in the National Football Conference championship 
game. Cincinnati defeated Buffalo, 21-10, for the American Football Conference 
title. 
</P>
<P>
The Super Bowl will be played Jan. 22 in Miami. 
</P>
<P>
San Francisco defeated Cincinnati, 26-21, in the 1982 Super Bowl and holds a 
5-1 edge in games with the Bengals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
