</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pasadena-based Beverly Enterprises Inc. has agreed to sell its 20 Massachusetts 
nursing homes to GHM Inc. of East Hartford, Conn. The transaction, involving 
1,797 beds, for $47.25 million includes 1,446 beds that are owned in 16 homes 
and 351 beds that are leased in four homes. The sale is subject to the approval 
of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts' Department of Public Health's division of 
health-care quality. Beverly Chairman Robert Van Tuyle said the move is part of 
the company's restructuring, which was announced last spring. He said the sale 
to GHM is scheduled to close this spring. 
</P>
