<P>
Beazer PLC said its Koppers Co. subsidiary has sold its Irwindale quarry and 
ancillary plant and Thiem Corp. for a total of about $67 million. Beazer, the 
British-American home building, contracting and building materials company, 
said United Rock Products Corp. purchased the quarry and plant. Thiem supplies 
adhesives and sealants for the automotive industry and refractories and 
chemicals for the foundry industry. It is being purchased by National Starch 
and Chemical Corp. of Bridgewater, N.J. 
