<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SOVIET UPSET IN TENNIS TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SYDNEY, Australia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
West German Christian Saceanu upset second-seeded Andrei Chesnokov of the 
Soviet Union 4-6, 6-4, 6-4 today in the first round of the $350,000 New South 
Wales Open. 
</P>
<P>
Romanian-born Saceanu, 20, went for broke in the final set, out-slugging 
Chesnokov, the loser in last year's title match. 
</P>
<P>
Olivier Delaitre, a French-born resident of Belgium, also ousted Jonas Svensson 
of Sweden 6-2, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
Two other seeded players, No. 4 Aaron Krickstein of the United States and 
sixth-seeded South African Christo van Rensburg, advanced to the last 16. 
Top-seeded Henri Leconte of France did not play today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
