<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
10 MORE RACE DRIVERS EARN A MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SPARTANBURG, S.C. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Second-generation NASCAR stock car star Davey Allison is among 10 drivers who 
joined the list of racing millionaires in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
The 10 new entries, tying the record for the most drivers to climb over $1 
million in career earnings in a single year, raised to 70 the number in the 
group. 
</P>
<P>
Besides Allison, who reached the $1-million plateau in 57 events -- the fastest 
pace in NASCAR history -- the list includes Brazilian Indy-car and endurance 
racer Raul Boesel, Indy-car drivers Howdy Holmes, Derek Daly, Tony 
Bettenhausen, Scott Brayton and Johnny Parsons Jr., and NASCAR regulars Lake 
Speed, Phil Parsons and Sterling Marlin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
